params._finder: UMA protocol Finder used to discover other protocol contracts.
params._timer: Contract that stores the current time in a testing environment.
params._tokenFactory: ERC20 token factory used to deploy synthetic token instances.

params.collateralPerPair: how many units of collateral are required to mint one pair of synthetic tokens.
params.collateralToken: ERC20 token used as as collateral in the LSP.
params.customAncillaryData: Custom ancillary data to be passed along with the price request. If not needed, this                             should be left as a 0-length bytes array.
params.expirationTimestamp: unix timestamp of when the contract will expire.
params.prepaidProposerReward: Proposal reward to be forwarded to the created contract to be used to incentivize price proposals.
params.priceIdentifier: registered in the DVM for the synthetic.
params.syntheticName: Name of the synthetic tokens to be created. The long tokens will have "Long Token" appended     to the end and the short token will "Short Token" appended to the end to distinguish within the LSP's tokens.
params.syntheticSymbol: Symbol of the synthetic tokens to be created. The long tokens will have "l" appended     to the start and the short token will "s" appended to the start to distinguish within the LSP's tokens.

returns._0: uint for the current Testable timestamp.

setCurrentTime(uint256).details: Will revert if not running in test mode.

params.time: timestamp to set current Testable time to.

createLongShortPair(uint64,uint256,bytes.notice: The created LSP is NOT registered within the registry as the LSP contract uses the DVM.The LSP constructor does a number of validations on input params. These are not repeated here.

getCurrentTime().notice: Gets the current time. Will return the last time set in `setCurrentTime` if running in test mode. Otherwise, it will return the block timestamp.

userdoc.notice: Factory contract to create and register new instances of long short pair contracts. Responsible for constraining the parameters used to construct a new LSP. These constraints can evolve over time and are initially constrained to conservative values in this first iteration.
